Commentary: Currently only an older version is available. On the starting page,a note says "The British Women Romantic Poets archive is being transitioned to a new home. This page will automatically redirect to the new location when it becomes available.";
Homepage: "Last content update May 23,2001."

Proposal: "Poetess Archive (flowery poetry written in Britain and America between 1750–1900)"
Homepage: "Work Flow: Every bibliographic entry in the Poetess Archive has been made into a TEI-encoded page (see "Editorial Principles" for more about TEI). We have created TEI templates and will continue to create them for those who wish to submit texts already encoded,but we accept submissions of any kind,and then TEI-encode them here. After that work,the TEI pages are:
- created into HTML presenetation pages;
- entered into our Oracle database;
- made into RDFs so that the Poetess Archive Database is interoperable with NINES using the NINES COLLEX TOOL."
